{{Infobox company |name = Compagnie des Cristalleries de Saint Louis |logo = |type = part of [[Hermès International S.A.]] |foundation = 1767 |location = [[Saint-Louis-lès-Bitche]], [[Lorraine (region)|Lorraine]], France |area_served = Worldwide |key_people = |industry = |products = [[glass]] |revenue = [[Euro|€]] |operating_income = |net_income = |assets = |equity = |num_employees = |homepage = [http://www.saint-louis.com/en www.saint-louis.com] }} [[File:Nef by St Louis Crystal.jpg|thumb|left|Saint Louis French Crystal Nef Centerpiece exhibited at the [[Exposition Universelle (1889)|1889 Exposition Universelle]] in Paris. Circa 1887]] The '''Compagnie des Cristalleries de Saint Louis''' is a [[corporation]], founded in 1767 in Münzthal ([[Saint-Louis-lès-Bitche]] in French) in [[Lorraine (region)|Lorraine]]. It is the oldest glass manufacturer in France with roots dating back to 1586 and the first [[Lead glass|crystal glass]] manufacturer in continental Europe (1781).
The '''Musée du cristal Saint-Louis''' exhibits 4 centuries of technical developments and artistic creations of the Saint-Louis factory. It is housed in one of the production halls of the factory, in Saint-Louis-lès-Bitche.<ref>[http://www.saint-louis.com/en/museum/la-grande-place.html Museum website]</ref>
